column5: Looking for a pwr auger , any advise between the 2 brands??

If the only choices I had were between.. Strikemaster or Eskimo....   I'd get the Eskimo.  A ton of my friends have Eskimos and love them.  I had the chance to try a Strikemaster last winter and @ - 25 it didn't wanna start.  But.... My first choice is a Jiffy.   RFS
Strikemaster is way better then the Eskimo, but I wish I never sold my jiffy!!
Agreed!!!  Actually, I wish I sold my Jiffy.........mine kinda got "donated" to the old man.............along with my portable hut!!! Its too bad he's 3000km from me  S.
Jiffy all the way!  Two of my friends have strikemasters and i have my holes cut before they even get thiers started!
I'm going to say Jiffy also.
